{"type":"message","id":"c8f6c352","parentId":"d4b77153","timestamp":"2026-04-09T03:04:27.143Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"It seems there's an issue with retrieving recent AI news summaries from the web. The function `web_search` is intended to fetch information based on a search query, but it requires access to the Brave Search API key for that functionality.\n\nTo resolve this, you would need to set up and configure the Brave Search API key in your OpenClaw environment. This can be done by running the following command:\n\n```bash\nopenclaw configure --section web\n```\n\nThis will prompt you to enter or accept the API key necessary for performing searches using Brave's search engine.\n\nOnce that is configured, you should be able to retrieve recent AI news summaries as requested in your previous query. If setting up the API key poses any issues or additional steps are needed, feel free to ask, and I'll assist further.\n"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"qwen-local:latest","usage":{"input":8184,"output":164,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":8348,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775703867138}}
